    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Encapsulates the asynchronous execution of a callable. Future instances are created by Executor.submit() and should not be created directly except for testing. cancel()¶ Attempt to cancel the call. If the call is currently being executed or finished running and cannot be cancelled then the method will return False, otherwise the call will be cancelled and the method will return True. cancelled()¶ Return True if the call was successfully cancelled. running()¶ Return True if the call is current..."
